    #touorgx9WdrBLoK4lslBqbO6 ^"Spell Scroll" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Item"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Item Type" STRING "Scroll"
            ^"Rarity" STRING "varies"
            ^"Description" STRING "A spell scroll bears the words of a single spell, written in a mystical cipher. If the spell is on your class's spell list, you can read the scroll and cast its spell without providing any material components. Otherwise, the scroll is unintelligible. Casting the spell by reading the scroll requires the spell's normal casting time. Once the spell is cast, the words on the scroll fade, and it crumbles to dust. If the casting is interrupted, the scroll is not lost. If the spell is on your class's spell list but of a higher level than you can normally cast, you must make an ability check using your spellcasting ability to determine whether you cast it successfully. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a failed check, the spell disappears from the scroll with no other effect. The level of the spell on the scroll determines the spell's saving throw DC and attack bonus, as well as the scroll's rarity, as shown in the Spell Scroll table.

**Spell Scroll.** A cantrip spell is Common rarity, with a save DC of 13 and attack bonus of +5. A 1st-level spell is Common, save DC 13, attack bonus +5. A 2nd-level spell is Uncommon, save DC 13, attack bonus +5. A 3rd-level spell is Uncommon, save DC 15, attack bonus +7. A 4th-level spell is Rare, save DC 15, attack bonus +7. A 5th-level spell is Rare, save DC 17, attack bonus +9. A 6th-level spell is Very rare, save DC 17, attack bonus +9. A 7th-level spell is Very rare, save DC 18, attack bonus +10. An 8th-level spell is Very rare, save DC 18, attack bonus +10. A 9th-level spell is Legendary, save DC 19, attack bonus +11.

A wizard spell on a *spell scroll* can be copied just as spells in spellbooks can be copied. When a spell is copied from a *spell scroll*, the copier must succeed on an Intelligence (Arcana) check with a DC equal to 10 + the spell's level. If the check succeeds, the spell is successfully copied. Whether the check succeeds or fails, the *spell scroll* is destroyed."
        }
    }
