                STRING "*Ranged Weapon Attack:* +3 to hit, range 100/400 ft., one target. *Hit:* 6 (1d10 + 1) piercing damage."
            }
        }
    }
    SPEC_VERSION "0.4"
    # Third-party D&D 5e setting book (Historica Arcanum: The City of Crescent).
    # It is a composition-set EXTENSION of the dnd5e base edition: its content
    # files reuse the base framework types (Spell, Magic Item, Feat, Monster,
    # Subclass, Background) declared in Dnd5e_Core_Base, and this file adds the
    # THREE new subsystem type families the book introduces on top of 5e:
    # 1. The Profession System  (PEX, ranks, perks)
    # 2. Spell Rebound          (the setting's "magic has a price" subsystem)
    # 3. Magic Origins          (the setting's six origins of magic)
    # Instances live in sibling historica-coc-0.4-*.ttrpg files.
    # ============================================================
    # MAGIC ORIGINS (section 01 - "Origin of Magic")
    # ============================================================
    #cocMagicOrigin00001 ^"Magic Origin" DEF {
        # One of the setting's six origins of magic, each tied to the D&D 5e
        # classes that draw on it. Flavor/lore prose lives in the companion
        # .lore; the queryable mapping (origin -> classes) is structured here.
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING
            ^"Description" STRING
        }
    }
    # ============================================================
    # THE PROFESSION SYSTEM (section 09)
    # ============================================================
    #cocProfession000001 ^"Profession" DEF {
        APPLIES TO [^"Character"]
        # A profession a character can take (one only), gaining Profession
        # Experience (PEX) to buy ranks and perks. A profession instance supplies
        # its CR->PEX earning schedule in a PEX_TABLE sub-block (^"PEX Award"
        # entries) and its rank tiers in a RANKS sub-block (^"Profession Rank"
        # entries, each with a PERKS sub-block of ^"Profession Perk").
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING
            ^"Overview" STRING
            ^"Aspiring Background" STRING
        }
    }
    #cocPexAward00000001 ^"PEX Award" DEF {
        # One row of a profession's Challenge Rating -> PEX earning table.
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Challenge Rating" STRING
            ^"PEX" INTEGER MIN 0
        }
    }
    #cocProfRank00000001 ^"Profession Rank" DEF {
        # A rank tier within a profession (Apprentice=1, Journeyman=2, ...). Its
        # purchasable perks live in a PERKS sub-block of ^"Profession Perk".
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Rank Number" INTEGER MIN 1
            ^"Description" STRING
        }
    }
    #cocProfPerk00000001 ^"Profession Perk" DEF {
        # A perk purchasable with PEX at a given rank. Some perks present an
        # internal "choose one of" — that choice text is kept whole in the
        # description (completeness over structure).
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"PEX Cost" INTEGER MIN 0
            ^"Description" STRING
        }
    }
    # ============================================================
    # SPELL REBOUND (section 06 - "A Vengeful Reality and Magic Untamed")
    # ============================================================
    #tdE1YCwELPQChb3kxVDKCOAW ^"Spell Rebound" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "Magic comes at a price. A GM may want to include these rules in a game set in the World of Historica Arcanum to show why magic is considered dangerous universally and add some consequence to spell casting.

Core Mechanic: In the table below, a trigger for a Spell Rebound is shown depending on the caster's proficiency bonus. However, a GM may deem a situation to be appropriate for a Spell Rebound.

*The usual maximum proficiency bonus for a player character is +6. Some creatures may have higher proficiency bonus than that, such as a lich or an ancient red dragon, but those kinds of immensely powerful creatures are very rare or nonexistent at all in the Historica Arcanum universe.

**For warlocks, this trigger is considered as \"Casting a spell that is provided with Eldritch Invocations, such as casting detect magic through eldritch sight, casting magic armor through armor of shadows, or other similar situations.\"

***Such as casting the magic missile spell on its own initiative count and casting the shield spell at another creature's turn but during the same round.

Triggers are cumulative. If a creature has +4 proficiency bonus, the triggers for lower proficiency bonuses apply as well.

Trigger: The character makes a saving throw using the same ability used for spellcasting. For example, a wizard makes an Intelligence saving throw because the wizard's spellcasting ability is Intelligence. The DC equals the character's own spell save DC. On a failed save, consult the Effects table below. On a successful save, nothing happens, and the character cannot trigger the same Spell Rebound until it finishes a long rest (A creature that fails can trigger the effects again). If it can trigger it by another means, the trigger will happen again. For example, a 5th level wizard casting a fireball triggers the spell rebound. When the wizard expends their last spell slot, the spell rebound is triggered again.

If a creature has two separate spellcasting ability scores due to multiclassing, taking a feat or other reasons, the source of the spell determines the ability score. If a spell somehow comes from separate sources at once, use the highest DC possible.

Some situations can cause more than one trigger, so each one requires its own saving throw.

Effects: There are three types of effects: Cosmetic, Destructive, and Internal. Cosmetic effects usually do not harm creatures or affect nearby objects or constructs in the means of dealing damage, but it may bring many social or similar consequences with them. Destructive effects usually damage nearby people and/or objects, possibly including the caster. Internal effects usually only affect the caster.

There are alternative ways to determine which category of effect occurs:

• A GM may roll a d6 and choose which categorical effect occurs. 1-2: Destructive 3-4: Internal 5-6: Cosmetic

• It may depend on the school of magic the spell that triggers the effect. A GM may choose a different category from the ones listed below: Abjuration: Internal Conjuration: Destructive Divination: Cosmetic Enchantment: Cosmetic Evocation: Destructive Illusion: Cosmetic Necromancy: Internal Transmutation: Internal

• The GM may decide which category to use depending on the triggering spell's theme, effect, or type. For example, a healing word spell may cause internal damage, while a damaging spell could cause destructive damage. A necromancy spell may cause internal damage regardless.

• It may depend on the situation. If the caster tries to harm someone, the effect could be internal. If the caster is deceiving someone, the effect could be cosmetic.

The Exceptions:
1. Some spells are ignored when its casting coincides with a trigger: detect magic, identify, lesser restoration, dispel magic, counterspell and antimagic field.
2. Casting a spell that is 4th level or higher from a spell scroll always causes a trigger.
3. Using a class feature or a similar effect that enables a creature to cast a spell of 3rd level or higher or expending a spell slot of 3rd level or higher directly causes a trigger. For example, mystic arcanum of a warlock, divine smite (3rd level or higher) of a paladin.
4. Casting a 9th level spell or expending a 9th level spell slot is counted as another destructive trigger, no matter what the spell is."
        }
        TRIGGERS {
            #t4NAnnA7odIYohu1TM7nc494 ^"Trigger +2" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+2"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Expending all spell slots."
            }
            #tKvtFZyAuL17CCtA7GCtnssh ^"Trigger +3" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+3"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Expending a highest level spell slot.**"
            }
            #t98Z44ddaWtU2EHacMtIHNEJ ^"Trigger +4" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+4"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Casting two spells in successive rounds or in the same round***. Cantrips do not count."
            }
            #tdFckjokOZ2HPnsXpRJBgNIy ^"Trigger +5" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+5"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Casting a spell that includes a damage roll. Such as fireball, magic missile, blight, and scorching ray. Cantrips do not count."
            }
            #tXCmyPRul2zQKOL8yoheiDDy ^"Trigger +6" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+6"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Casting a spell of 6th level or higher."
            }
            #t2gDtSQr5sdMIfgmkhqFtLlp ^"Trigger +7 or higher*" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Trigger"
                ^"Proficiency Bonus"
                STRING "+7 or higher*"
                ^"Trigger"
                STRING "Dropping a creature to 0 hit points with a spell, magical ability, a supernatural feature or the like or restoring life to a creature while it is on 0 hit points with a spell or a similar magical effect."
            }
        }
        EFFECTS {
            #tMXmNJ8yhynuVAFPJNDFXlkD ^"Cosmetic 1" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "1"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Stutter: The caster stutters for the next 3d6 hours. Disadvantage on spell attack rolls for the duration (Spells with verbal component). The greater restoration spell ends this effect early."
            }
            #tipZyiNoFBuONO22QrogocC1 ^"Cosmetic 2" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "2"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Bodily Dysfunction. The caster suffers a malevolent effect that badly affects the body. For example, if the leg is affected, the caster may suffer a limp and thus have his walking speed reduced to half. It lasts for 3d4 days."
            }
            #tHk08umX7LkAJiTj7j0ZXoC1 ^"Cosmetic 3" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "3"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Rot. Vegetables and plants within 120 ft. of the caster wither and die. It lasts 2d6 days. Bathing under the moonlight reduces the area to 30 ft for the next 24 hours."
            }
            #t79uo4nBcePxsrnYdPYREvtv ^"Cosmetic 4" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "4"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Pale Skin. The caster appears sickly and extremely pale. It lasts 2d6 days. The greater restoration spell ends this effect early."
            }
            #t4tCPCCs3CqKuUufaJnxTuLG ^"Cosmetic 5" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "5"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Glow in the Dark. The caster's eyes or other limbs (for example, their hand) glow in total darkness. It lasts for 3d4 days. Drinking water from a river during sunset negates this effect until midnight."
            }
            #tOx5MA6eTvh9PQa6lu1L1oIV ^"Cosmetic 6" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "6"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Scar. The caster receives a scar determined by the GM. It can't be removed. The scar can only be removed with a greater restoration spell that is cast from an 8th-level or higher spell scroll."
            }
            #t5hEeUVd3ziHJwNBgXwNLoFW ^"Cosmetic 7" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "7"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Wild Despise. The wild seems to despise the caster. Wild beasts are aggressive towards them, and urban animals are terrified of them. Dogs and cats alike usually hiss and growl at the caster. Chewing a three-leaf clover at the start of the day reduces the aggressiveness of the beasts."
            }
            #tsxLgm6epToQkgTzauRZjJ7R ^"Cosmetic 8" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "8"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Shaking Hands. The caster's hands start to shake, and it constantly gets worse. The caster has disadvantage on Dexterity or Strength check that is related to the hands. It lasts for 2d4 days."
            }
            #tNjf5cDJTzTVEH4fSWNa4meb ^"Cosmetic 9" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "9"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Constant Cold. The caster constantly feels cold and appears to be shivering. While in extreme heat, this effect is not seen."
            }
            #tJH2BpCvMhdvHtuNrFtMYsVR ^"Cosmetic 10" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Cosmetic"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "10"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Reflection Mishap. The caster's reflection in proper surfaces may occur differently, such as facing in the wrong direction, doing something else entirely: crying, appearing angry or appearing extremely happy. These mishaps usually happen briefly, for mere seconds, and disappear. These effects can be seen for 2d8 days."
            }
            #tCLDRx8fCOaosNnysEwAtRJ0 ^"Destructive 1" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "1"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Hellfire: The flames erupt from you as if you are bringing the fire itself from the depths of Tartarus. Any object that is flammable catches fire within 120 ft. of the caster. Each creature within 120 ft. must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 5d6 fire damage. Each proficiency bonus after +2 adds another 2d6 fire damage. A counterspell stops this effect if the triggering spell is 3rd level or lower. If it is higher, the DC equals to 10 + spell slot's level."
            }
            #t7bAUYINWnpCOoYO3NblxUkD ^"Destructive 2" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "2"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Quake: The ground shakes. Each creature within 300 ft. must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or fall prone. For the next minute the shake continues and standing up requires another Dexterity saving throw. Each fail results in 1d6 bludgeoning damage. Each proficiency bonus after +2 deals another 2d6 damage."
            }
            #tE7en97LXgW5TmF4b5wm6R3D ^"Destructive 3" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "3"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Blinding Light: A bright light erupts from the caster. Each creature within 120 ft. of the caster must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be blinded. At the end of each day, the affected creatures can make another saving throw to be free from the effect. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #ttZWyaDY50e3fJ6BezuVEADd ^"Destructive 4" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "4"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Deafening Sound: A horrible scream, a crash of thunder, or another loud noise is heard within 300 ft. of the caster. Each creature within the area must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be deafened. At the end of each day, the affected creatures can make another saving throw to be free from the effect. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #t4JjEYX3KMfo8QEN9zcju1aM ^"Destructive 5" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "5"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Poison Aura: A foul stench overwhelms you. Each creature within 60 ft. of the caster must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be poisoned for the next 4d6 hours, and they take 3d6 poison damage (damage occurs only once). Each proficiency bonus after +2 deals another 2d6 damage. The stench stays in the area for the next 2d4 hours. Each creature that enters the area or starts its turn there must make the saving throw. A lesser restoration or a greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #tuyALow7PKfZ2m2ifdwe8LGy ^"Destructive 6" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "6"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Smell of Mortem: A feeling of dread and the impending doom of time surrounds the area. Each creature within 120 ft. of the caster must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or age 1d6 x 5 years. The magical aura stays there for 24 hours. Each creature that enters the area or starts its turn there must make the saving throw. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #ta1tpwgYY7dpa9N2px1tukHD ^"Destructive 7" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "7"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "March of the Dead. A loud heartbeat fills the caster's mind and creates an aura within 300 ft. of it. Dead creatures within the aura become undead creatures proper to their state and body. The creatures in the aura take 1d6 necrotic damage at the start of each of their turns or when they enter the first time; the undead are immune to this. The undead created by this aura are relentless and attack everyone on sight. If no creature has become undead, a blast within the area deals each creature 2d6 necrotic damage. A touch of a believer immediately destroys the undead if it is CR 1/4 or lower."
            }
            #t1tRP6gT1FafdqlwDwod59nC ^"Destructive 8" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "8"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Thunderous Hands. A flash of lightning erupts from the caster. Each creature within 120 ft. of the caster must succeed on DC 15 Constitution saving throw or take 3d6 lightning damage. The creatures that have failed take extra 1d6 lightning damage whenever they touch a metal object. This effect lasts for 2d4 days. Spending a long rest on a soil that at least one believer prayed on will end the effect early."
            }
            #tyYyX2DENumRFXa4NGmcDYm4 ^"Destructive 9" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "9"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Enduring Cold. The reign of foretold winter in the ancient myths comes to life within 120 ft. of the caster. Each creature within range must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or take 3d6 cold damage, or half of it on a successful save. Each proficiency bonus after +2 adds another 2d6 cold damage. The cold aura persists after the first blast. If a creature enters the aura for the first time or starts its turn there, it takes 1d6 cold damage. A counterspell stops this effect if the triggering spell is 3rd level or lower. If it is higher, the DC equals to 10 + spell slot's level."
            }
            #tSNuCRHiMxbmCq82OViSJ4qQ ^"Destructive 10" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Destructive"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "10"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "Aura of Nightmare: A voice from the apocalypse reaches out from the depths with a vision of terror. Each creature within 120 ft. of the caster must succeed on a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, they see random visions and hallucinations. In addition, whenever they attempt a long rest, they must succeed on a DC 10 Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, they can't benefit from a long rest, as their sleep is haunted by terrible nightmares. Starting the long rest while having the good will and/or the blessing of an innocent creature gives the caster an advantage on the saving throw."
            }
            #tExszUzDPppHfG6ojTIsyl5U ^"Internal 1" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "1"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster has disadvantage on saving throws for the next 1d6 hours."
            }
            #t6JTVobu279pxfvBiXKq6prb ^"Internal 2" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "2"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster gains two levels of exhaustion. A greater restoration spell reduces all exhaustion related to spell rebound."
            }
            #t3fk6J4xgvnd0A0QyiLYTbP7 ^"Internal 3" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "3"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster can't cast a spell for the next 3d6 hours. This includes cantrips and features like divine smite. If the caster receives an inspiration, it can spend it to cast a spell. A spell cast this way must be 3rd level or lower."
            }
            #tfA0u1WHuWD40bsX9tE9d82H ^"Internal 4" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "4"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster can't gain any benefit from a short or long rest for the next 1d6 days. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #t4GeMwuyLPMgGtxL2lZAUA9k ^"Internal 5" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "5"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster's spell save DC is reduced by 1d4 for the next 24 hours. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #tcmE1IGgMLSltEL0jmdif9zK ^"Internal 6" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "6"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster has a short term memory loss. It lasts for 4d6 hours. If the caster receives a hug or a kiss from a loved one, the effect ends early (minimum of 1 hour)"
            }
            #tgHWnioWi0eX8ugM2K1rXZQR ^"Internal 7" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "7"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster loses the ability to move one of their limbs. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #tlEDEjxsspue3NI49R20ydOm ^"Internal 8" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "8"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster loses the ability to see or to hear for the next 24 hours."
            }
            #tQpc0cR0COuVWSpI1wsaRpoK ^"Internal 9" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "9"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster's maximum HP is reduced by 1d6. Each proficiency bonus after +2 reduces it for another 3d6. For example, a creature with +4 proficiency loses 7d6 maximum HP. A greater restoration spell reverses this effect."
            }
            #taDF3gHul9xg5lFlIVjesIQ4 ^"Internal 10" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Spell Rebound Effect"
                ^"Category"
                STRING "Internal"
                ^"Roll"
                STRING "10"
                ^"Effect"
                STRING "The caster is driven mad in a way determined by the GM."
            }
        }
    }
    #cocReboundTrigger01 ^"Spell Rebound Trigger" DEF {
        # One rung of the proficiency-bonus trigger ladder: at this proficiency
        # bonus, the given situation triggers a Spell Rebound. Triggers are
        # cumulative (higher bonuses also suffer all lower triggers).
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Proficiency Bonus" STRING
            ^"Trigger" STRING
        }
    }
    #cocReboundEffect001 ^"Spell Rebound Effect" DEF {
        # One rollable Spell Rebound effect within a category (Cosmetic,
        # Destructive, or Internal).
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Category" STRING
            ^"Roll" STRING
            ^"Effect" STRING
        }
    }
    # ============================================================
    # NEW WEAPON PROPERTIES (section 03 - firearms)
    # ============================================================
    #cocWeaponProperty01 ^"Weapon Property" DEF {
        # A weapon property this setting adds on top of the D&D 5e list, used by
        # the firearms in historica-coc-0.4-equipment.ttrpg.
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING
        }
    }
    #cocWpnPropReload001 ^"Reload" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Weapon Property"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "This ability determines how much ammunition can be spent without using an attack or an action to reload the weapon. It is shown like this: Reload (6)"
        }
    }
    #cocWpnPropGunpowdr1 ^"Gunpowder" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Weapon Property"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "All martial firearm weapons have the gunpowder property; when you roll the maximum amount of damage in damage die, you reroll the die and add it to the resulting damage."
        }
    }
    # ============================================================
    # DJINN INTERACTION RULES (section 20 - "Djinnkind")
    # ============================================================
    #cocDjinnRule0000001 ^"Djinn Rule" DEF {
        # One of the djinn-interaction subsystems that accompany the bestiary's
        # Djinnkind material: Possession for the Djinn, Exorcism Sacrament,
        # Djinnstruck, and Name of the Djinn. Each is a self-contained rule
        # (saving throws, DCs, ritual requirements) kept whole in ^"Description".
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING
        }
    }
    SPEC_VERSION "0.4"
    #tvuy5lqRgoZefO0VgpBzbVr6 ^"Arcane Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Wizard"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Lore of the Arcane**

Magic is said to be the driving force of the entropy of the universe, the source of instability of laws of nature. If harnessed correctly, it can grant physical strength, emotional connection, mental focus, spiritual alignment, energetic vitalization, and all sorts of miraculous feats. Yet to harness such powers demands disciplined hard work.

Practitioners have identified many different aspects to cast spells with arcane magic. To become a powerful practitioner of arcane magic, any aspiring arcanist needs to be dynamic and harmonious with at least some of the aspects of the arcane. Spellcasters with differing origins may also tap into several aspects of the arcane.

**Aspects of Arcane**

**Abjuration** school is dedicated to protective magic, the magic that cancels or interferes with other kinds of magic, supernatural energies and effects through twisting the reality’s natural protection against arcane.

**Alteration** and **Transmutation** schools are dedicated to the skill to transform one form of matter into another, using magic to transform the molecular nature of matter.

**Conjuration** and **Summoning** schools are dedicated to spontaneous transportation or manifesting of creatures, energies, objects into reality, by tapping into a wizard's creative energy and twisting the flow of time and space.

**Divination** school is dedicated to acquiring or exposing information about the unknown and the future. Arcanists achieve this feat by not pulling knowledge from the future itself, but through manifesting an otherwise unexplorable wisdom hidden in their minds. However, existence of other diviners within reach may cloud the manifestation capabilities of diviners.

**Enchantment** or **Charm** schools are dedicated to beguiling the minds of others to make them do the things you want. Such a feat is accomplished by manipulating the sensory perceptions and the nervous system of the victim through the use of arcane abilities.

**Evocation** school is dedicated to creating matter and energy out of nothing by forcing reality into submission, and altering the nature of the elements existing near the caster.

**Illusion** and **Phantasm** schools are dedicated to changing the appearance of something by manifesting images, hallucinations and deception. The magic achieves the desired effect by manipulating matters’ visibility through arcane.

**Necromancy** is dedicated to spells which involve death, undeath and the manipulation of the energy of life. There are many methods of casting necromantic spells, such as manipulating the time flow in a single object, or a body, to rewind death and injury."
        }
    }
    #tnVH7CEUGeOaazDtraBxmwKx ^"Divine Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Cleric", "Paladin"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Rules of Divinity**

The ancient tablets, parchments and scrolls on divine magic written by the priests of old describe divine magic as a solemn understanding between a greater power and a mortal being. They describe this relationship as a symbiosis: the greater power rejoices the faith of the believer and in return provides the miracles to one in need. However, some arcane researchers dwell on an entirely different idea that these pious people take their power to create miracles only through their willpower and creed. In either case, their miracles can be used to heal the wounded, bless the miserable, return sight to the sightless and guide people through hardships. They appear in history as miracle workers, prodigies of the holy, and wielders of the scripture.

Divine magic is direct, predictable, and easy to accept when viewed by an educated witness in the matters of the occult. It may be holy or dark, benign or catastrophic, depending on the person performing the miracles. If a believer somehow loses her faith or starts to walk in a completely different path, it is said that the greater power either curses her or stops granting miracles to her. More credible researchers interpose this idea by saying that the loss of power is due to the caster losing belief in themselves.

**Origin of Divinity**

The knowledge passed from generation to generation on divine magic describes its origin as such: “It is granted by a beneficent, abusive, or egoistical greater power bearing the capability to grant miracles.” Some researchers contradict this idea by dictating that the origin of divine magic comes from the very souls each person possesses. Research made on rural areas brings into our view that in some rare cases divine power appears in cases like prolonged delusion, abuse of hallucinogenic mushrooms, and even manifests under mental duress too. Throughout history the world has seen many different cults, beliefs, and religions supporting many different approaches to the origin of their own powers, and who can say which idea is correct?

Holy offerings, incense, and holy symbols are the usual offerings for divine spells, but in some cases, it has been seen that some acolytes pray upon profane religions offering live sacrifices as well.

**The Never-ending Path**

In Historica Arcanum, the work of a pious character never ends. The belief in the existence of celestial concepts took a hit among the masses during the Industrial Age. The practitioners of the divine powers are quite rare, and mundane people do not have the educated eye to notice them in more modern times. There may be trouble in following the path of the pious, but it is a path that is worth following."
        }
    }
    #tNbtQjyCL0f6lcuyDrkTcwv6 ^"Inherent Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Sorcerer"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Fiery Blood**

Some magic isn't earned by hard work, endless hours of study or understanding of the arcane; some magic is inherent in the blood passed from many ancestors and received by the caster. In this aspect, the ancestor in question is mostly a creature or concept which has great power and spellcasting prowess. These kinds of spellcasters use the raw magic which burns in their veins. Such people bear a magical birthright descended to them from a bizarre or alien bloodline, some kind of otherworldly force or manifestation of a cosmic energy in them. These casters don't choose to be such, they are chosen to be as they are.

**Raw Potential**

Practitioners of inherent magic are rare to come by. They are always in a quest to unlock their raw potential or tap into the unknown limits of their powers. Such people soon discover that their power never stays dormant once awoken."
        }
    }
    #te45LqAA6XtdiXnCEuheGf7D ^"Inspirational Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Bard"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Authentic Artist**

Some magic manifests under the powers of song, art, or speech. This kind of arcane power is a lot more subtle. The performers of this kind of magic can inspire, arouse, excite, hearten, impress, influence, motivate, and provoke by the use of their magical song, inspirational speech or gorgeous art. It is said that the art of these magics is the reflection of words used during the creation of the universe; thus, the performers of such magic benefit from various kinds of different magics. In other words, this kind of magic is mostly based on art, stories, music and oratory skills and involves knowing a little bit from everything at a time but never grasping one subject wholly.

**Potent Troubadour**

This kind of magic can be used a lot more subtly compared with many other types. It can be hidden behind poems, songs, musical notes or even behind speeches. It is really easy for such a caster to inspire allies or cripple foes, alter how people think, cause confusion or create deception."
        }
    }
    #tobHz0t80T5J1fZCpvNIs9bE ^"Natural Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Druid", "Ranger"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Apostle of Terra Firma**

The magic of nature is perhaps the most pure of occult arts, yet it hosts great irony as you twist the laws of nature using nature itself. Texts passed down on obelisks, standing stones and other archaic information detail this kind of magic as a connection between forces of nature and a mortal capable of twisting the laws of nature to unleash the force. These arcane powers are harsh, raw and less refined than other aspects.

Nature magic is severe, sharp, acute, and to the point, as nature herself. Those with an educated eye and mind will perceive that this kind of magic rebounds on flora and fauna in a miniscule way.

**Roots of Augury**

According to the combined observations of and insight of sages through the ages, the amassed knowledge on nature magic describes it as such: ”The archaic forces of mother nature are granted by the so-called “ancient spirits of nature” to a select people who hear a call to the wilds. These ancient spirits are most likely a product of a person’s subconsciousness born with the inherent power of nature magic. The ways of these spellcasters are primitive and rigid as are the ways of nature.”"
        }
    }
    #toUYXamWGPYtECbbPgUGxB5S ^"Pact Magic" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Magic Origin"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Associated Classes" LIST OF STRING ["Warlock"]
            ^"Description" STRING "**Bonding Contracts**

The first users of the arcane were wizards, their powers and rebounds on the world gave birth to sorcerers. The combined magic in turn spawned beings of immense arcane instability, who can grant powers through pacts. Some arcanists seeking power or ways to fulfill their desires forge contracts with these patrons. In the dusty pages of history, magic influenced many supernatural creatures and allowed them to inflict great changes among the common folk. If one being’s desire and a supernatural being’s agenda fit, these contracts give them magical powers, allowing them to use magic even though they are not wizards who study the arcane, or sorcerers that inherit a great power.

**Invoking Arcana**

Creatures gain the ability to cast spells through pacts, and their bonding terms also invoke the mysterious powers in the arcane boundaries of magic. Their eldritch abilities seem mysterious even in the eyes of arcane masters. The chains of the pact makers may be broken if the creature on the receiving end reaches the peaks of mystic arcanum."
        }
    }
    SPEC_VERSION "0.4"
