                STRING "11"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 70
            }
            #tFkSKxIJCe6rkulqufHxg99j ^"The Bounty Hunter — CR 12" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "12"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 80
            }
            #tazOvNvmNKMLCQnCVcSMTmnz ^"The Bounty Hunter — CR 13" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "13"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 100
            }
            #tJxM3EjGhhYm18ovoISge02W ^"The Bounty Hunter — CR 14" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "14"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 120
            }
            #twJR3LH7PxMk79ftUQkUXm8b ^"The Bounty Hunter — CR 15-16" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "15-16"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 250
            }
            #thfS3kbjmDrvJMxmur9Jz1Yh ^"The Bounty Hunter — CR 17+" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "17+"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 600
            }
        }
        RANKS {
            #ttgZ0EEEr00SFfz7uVBcvL4s ^"Apprentice Bounty Hunter" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 1
                ^"Description"
                STRING "As an apprentice bounty hunter, you understand the basics of the hunt and can use simple but effective tactics; you choose one of the below:

You can advance into the Journeyman level after taking at least two apprentice-level tactics. Each tactic will cost you 50 PEX. You must have hunted at least one CR 5 bounty successfully in your career."
                PERKS {
                    #t6ljNMMpzM6vtiWmWZ8Cbpve ^"Advanced Tracking" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have the skills of a tracker when you are after your prey. Choose one of the following: Nature, Perception, or Investigation. Gain proficiency in it while you are tracking a foe."
                    }
                    #tt4CyPnOaBBbx5F9WbCLbMox ^"Smell the Ambush" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Your senses give you an edge when your prey decides to become your predator. In the first round of combat, if you are surprised, you gain +1 AC and advantage on saving throws against the cre ture which surprised you."
                    }
                    #tRayF9OjgPU2gn6IPXd50PlE ^"Tools of the Trade - Restock" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You can show your apprentice bounty hunter badge to get free equipment from any city or town which harbors a bounty hunter guild. If you need to restock your equipment, you can get one adventurer's pack, explorer's pack, or dungeoneer's pack; a quiver of bolts or arrows; a pair of light or finesse melee weapons; a bow or a crossbow; a single melee weapon; or a single suit of light armor. Abusing the use of this will get the bounty hunter banned for life from all the bounty hunter guilds."
                    }
                    #t9bvNB4hSWsrykLHTetIkYkK ^"Concoction - Long March" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You gain the skills to prepare a special bounty hunter remedy that focuses the senses and delays tiredness. Long March will grant the bounty hunter or anyone who imbibes it +10 movement for 1 hour when out of combat. However, only a person with bounty hunter training will benefit fully from this concoction: anyone else imbibing it will have a disadvantage on any skill checks for the duration of the effect. It takes two hours or one long rest to prepare one vial of Long March, and it costs 25 gold worth of herbs and spices."
                    }
                }
            }
            #toSUIp9lSpw2FfdgU25TPlGe ^"Journeyman Bounty Hunter" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(300PEX)

You are now a journeyman with some experience under your belt. You have worked rigorously and turned in bounty after bounty. Now you have a specialty: many encounters with monsters give you an edge against them.

You can advance to Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level tactics. Each tactic will cost you 100 PEX. You must have hunted at least one CR 9 bounty successfully in your career."
                PERKS {
                    #tRdGUyDUDAMJrlWwh4Og78Ia ^"Specialization Choice" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Trapper: The trapper knows how to use traps more efficiently. Any trap set by the trapper will deal an extra 1 die of its original damage on its original damage type.

Stalker: The stalker can hunt any beast or humanoid creature with more ease. You will have advantage on any Survival, Investigation, or Perception checks to track and find out information about their weaknesses and strengths."
                    }
                    #tYnL7L4eH9YMHDjkM17Ae0Mj ^"Know thy enemy" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "After countless encounters with many bounties, you start to gather common knowledge about them. Any Intelligence check you make to remember the vulnerabilities of a bounty will be made with advantage."
                    }
                    #tLThhvQpctErxRrIqF4PTXUU ^"Tools of the Trade - Armament" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You can show your journeyman bounty hunter badge and get more specialized equipment made for you at half the market price. Cold iron weapons against the fey or silvered weapons against lycanthropes are examples of this aspect."
                    }
                    #tjLyYVRBbozTNiyqqvSP16yJ ^"Accomplished Bloodhound" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The bounty hunter starts to get the grasp of the land, moving with greater ease and agility. During a hunt, the bounty hunter will not be hindered by any difficult terrain."
                    }
                    #tRhGchDhF58GQgJu6KdKW84b ^"Concoction - Exploit Weakness" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You gain skills to prepare a special bounty hunter remedy. Keen Eyesight will grant the bounty hunter and only the bounty hunter a d6 bonus on weapon attack damage for 1 minute. However, only a person with bounty hunter training will benefit fully from this concoction: anyone else imbibing it will have a disadvantage on any skill checks for the duration of the effect. It takes two hours or one long rest to prepare one vial of Exploit Weakness Concoction, and it costs 25 gold worth of uncommon herbs and spices, found in stores that sell uncommon crafting materials."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tumJPPjB8hdO2NyxNNtoMjTB ^"Expert Bounty Hunter" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(1000 PEX) You are now an expert with many years of experience amassed after many hard-earned bounties.

You can advance to Master level after taking at least two Expert level tactics. Each tactic will cost you 200 PEX. You must have hunted at least one CR 13 bounty successfully in your career."
                PERKS {
                    #t1BQXdc8rlm4OB1ZPLrihdFm ^"Resistance - Enchantment" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "After years of encounter after encounter, you start to get more durable against your quarry's magical powers. You gain advantage on saving throws against any enthralling power performed by your mark. Any magic or spell-like ability to affect your mind is considered enthrallment."
                    }
                    #twi8wGtuV9UIhviirRWN9ZF9 ^"Resistance - Dread" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "After years of encounter after encounter, you start to get more durable against your quarry's magical powers. You gain advantage on saving throws against any fear-related power performed against you by your mark."
                    }
                    #tOX608rkBjIrmLl97zGadvyW ^"Resistance - Affliction" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "After years of encounter after encounter, you start to get more durable against some of the afflictions your quarry might use against you. You gain advantage on any saving throws against blinded, deafened, grappled, prone and restrained conditions if they are afflicted by your mark."
                    }
                    #tWnaQwxfPxG59vMvfdTIv9hH ^"Resistance - Damage" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "After years of encounter after encounter, you start to get more durable against your quarry's special damage. When you accept a mark, you choose a damage type that your mark can deal and gain resistance against that type of damage for the duration of the hunt. You may have more than one bounty but you will only have one resistance at one given time."
                    }
                    #tpxx1BUBb6jncLqAsJhcsv9U ^"Concoction - Night Sight" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You gain skills to prepare a special bounty hunter remedy. Night sight will grant the bounty hunter the ability to see during the night and in dark spaces. The bounty hunter will gain 60 feet of darkvision. If the hunter already has darkvision, this amplifies the effect by 60 more feet. Only a person with bounty hunter training will benefit fully from this concoction: anyone else imbibing it will have a disadvantage on any skill checks for the duration of the effect. It takes two hours or a long rest to prepare one vial of Night Sight, and it costs 50 gold worth of herbs and spices."
                    }
                    #tYsmTuylIuhNfCeNUW3il3Qk ^"Tools of the Trade - Ultimate" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The bounty hunter guild allows you to purchase items from their specialist store. You gain the ability to purchase Antimagic Bolas, The Igniter Bomb, and the Bounty Hunter Armor. Each costs 1000 gold pieces.

Antimagic Bolas Weapon proficiency: Bounty Hunter. Properties: Range, Special Description: These bolas can be used against a large or a smaller creature. The creature is restrained until it is freed. It has no effect on formless creatures or creatures of huge or larger. A creature can use its action to make a DC 12 Strength (Athletics) check, freeing itself or another creature within its reach. Dealing 10 slashing damage to the bolas (AC 14) also frees the creature without harming it. Special Properties: While under the effect of the bolas, the target cannot perform any kind of magic.

The Igniter Bomb: Weapon Proficiency: Bounty Hunter. Properties: Explosive, Special. Description: This is a timed explosive that can be set for up to 10 minutes. Each creature in a 30-foot radius sphere centered on the bomb must make a dexterity saving throw (DC 14) A target takes 8d6 force damage on a failed save, or have as much damage on a successful one. Special Properties: This special weapon will also damage structures made of stone, wood and metal.

Bounty Hunter Armor: Armor Proficiency: Bounty Hunter. Armor Class: 18+ Dex (Max 1) Type: Heavy Armor Stealth: Disadvantage. Shield: Installed shield on one arm, both handsfree. With Shield AC is set to 20 (+1 Dex if applicable) Description: A very heavy armor, used very rarely because not many of these suits are left. Special Properties: While wearing this armor, the bludgeoning, slashing, and piercing damage from nonmagical weapons is reduced by 3."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tciaJn3sTtjTjMqPGCoWa36u ^"Master Bounty Hunter" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 4
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(5000 PEX) You are at the pinnacle of your profession. There is nothing much you can learn about the trade but you have much to share with your students."
                PERKS {
                    #tKWn688ETFjJ2tgMSsYalLBP ^"Stories of the Past" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have a lot of experiences, stories and have probably taken part in many of the legends and myths. You have the ability to inspire greatness in others. For a number of times daily equal to your proficiency bonus, you can grant inspiration to anyone who listens to your stories. This inspiration point must be used in 1 hour or it will be lost. Anyone who already has an inspiration point won't be affected by this."
                    }
                    #tRVdlRnZZeIljJqGSBzPUN0b ^"Leader of the Pack" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "In any bounty hunt you join, all the other characters will have the following benefits:

• Difficult terrain won't hinder them.

• The group won't be lost unless by magical means.

• The group will be alerted to danger, meaning they won't be subject to the surprised condition.

• When tracking your mark, you will gain information on the exact number of creatures around them."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    #t9vQXIdzWSTo7vX5F1RTxGyL ^"The Burglar" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Profession"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "A life of crime under the cover of darkness, and honing your skills in the art of thievery, extortion, breaking & entering, and swindling–Thieves, bandits, swindlers, prowlers, and robbers of all kinds fall under this profession. You are a burglar and earning your pay from the works of others is a day-to-day act for you."
            ^"Overview" STRING "How to Play? Decide on a mark, study how the mark acts during your free time. Find a weak or a sore spot and exploit it. Turn in the loot at a fence. Yet there will always be the forces of law trying to prevent you from getting your hard-earned gold. Be ready, be vigilant: it is not an easy life! Climbing the Ranks: For each act of thievery you perform, you gain PEX (Profession Experience) and when you gather enough PEX, you will advance in the ranks of the burglars. When you reach Rank 2 as a burglar you will have to be specialized in one way of theft. You earn PEX according to the gold pieces you earn from any type of heist. Each 10 gold pieces worth of stolen and fenced items will earn you 1 PEX."
            ^"Aspiring Background" STRING "You decide to spend your life as a burglar, and by taking this background, you can start this profession at level 1 with 0 PEX as an Apprentice Burglar. Proficiencies + Equipment. Skill Proficiencies: Stealth, Sleight of Hand. Languages: Any one of your choice. Tool Proficiencies: Thieves Tools. Equipment: Thieves Tools, a dark cloak, a crowbar and a pouch with 10 gp."
        }
        RANKS {
            #t0e9eLu90R7hJoee9WXqlimd ^"Apprentice Burglar" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 1
                ^"Description"
                STRING "As an apprentice burglar, you are versed with the basics of the “trade” and you know the simplest of the techniques; you will have to choose one from the below: You can advance into the Journeyman level after taking at least two Apprentice level techniques. Each technique will cost you 50 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tATHMerAH6ISbSARtV351iNy ^"Armament Coating" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You learn how to produce a black gooey substance to coat your weapons, armor, and other metal equipment with. It takes 10 minutes to apply it to all of your equipment. You will gain Stealth proficiency as long as your equipment is coated with this substance. The effect lasts two hours; after that, the goo will dry up and wither away. The goo is water-resistant. It takes 50 gp worth of herbs and materials to produce this dark goo."
                    }
                    #tBQW0VBPfpDIyS5xXiO2f9QS ^"Patient Stalking" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You carefully watch your heist target for 24 hours and gain exact information about their guard schedules, when they exchange guards, which guards are corrupt or loyal, which guards sleep on their duty, and which guards will accept bribes."
                    }
                    #tfglXOQredi8H6XatmrxGQZz ^"Hasty Exit" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Sometimes things don't go as planned and you will have to get ready to run for dear life. You have what it takes to jump off the second story of a building, pick yourself up and keep running if the job goes sour. If you are being chased during or after a heist, you will be able to flee with +5 to your movement. In addition, when you jump off a high location, the falling distance is calculated -10 feet for damage purposes."
                    }
                    #tVfj56nIgyokJAyvDfyvd0Zr ^"Safecracker’s Dream" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You become extremely proficient with cracking safes and opening locks. The difficulty of a lock you are fiddling with drops by one magnitude, essentially meaning that the DC is lowered by 5 (or based on GM discretion)."
                    }
                    #tF0Fh7Sskw4szUWlRYjbp3mH ^"Tools of the Trade - Restock" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You can get swindled stuff from the fences you know all around the city or a town that harbors a thieves’ guild. You pay half the price for these used, but still functional, items. If you need to restock your equipment, you can get one adventurer's pack, explorer's pack, or dungeoneer's pack; a quiver of bolts or arrows; a pair of light or finesse melee weapons; a bow or a crossbow; single melee weapon; oe a single suit of light armor. Abusing the use of this will mean that you will no longer be welcome in the black market as a burglar."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tuw5qgZPf42jHTI34FYNA6mJ ^"Journeyman Burglar" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "You are now a journeyman burglar and have some experience after making marks and stealing a small dragons’ hoard-worth of money. Now you have a specialty and in that specialty, you will have an edge. You can advance into the Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level techniques. Each technique will cost you 100 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #ttIYSl9eevU9kApplIk9ca65 ^"Specialization Choice" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have to choose one of the three: A Duskshadow who uses darkness as an ally, a Darkblade who knows that the dead can’t resist theft, and a Venomtongue who runs a more profitable criminal enterprise."
                    }
                    #txSsxckAWxMKcKRpoBkLDFqW ^"Ingenious Technique" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this method: Duskshadow: When using the Stealth skill, a Duskshadow will use half the movement speed (as is usually the case with stealth) and will gain +5 feet on top of that. Darkblade: A Shadowblade will gain the ability to use sneak attacks, regardless of class, for d6 extra damage. If the character already has the skills to sneak attack, this d6 is added on top of the damage. Venomtongue: A Venomtongue is a master con man who is great at selling stolen and second-hand items. Usually, 1/2 of the market price is used for used items for stolen and used items, but for the Venomtongue 3/4 is used."
                    }
                    #tnGQbRllTV4LFFRrzhRE9T0w ^"Tools of the Trade - Bags" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method and learn to use the Specialized Bags. The burglars need to be prepared to carry more stuff when they get into a heist. A character can carry an amount of weight equal to their Strength multiplied by 15 pounds at maximum, but in this special case, because of the specialized bags, this calculation is done as Strength multiplied by 20."
                    }
                    #thKAnIlT5uH2f21nbUFPIpbl ^"Efficient Bribing" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method. The burglar knows how to deal with the guards and other people who protect the heist. When you try to coerce anyone during a heist into doing what you want by paying a bribe, you will have advantage on your Perception checks. The burglar needs to offer a bribe acceptable by the GM to the person in question."
                    }
                    #tLpCP7XWECHOtNhrwPSjR09W ^"Eye of the Appraiser" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The burglar needs to have a trained eye to see what is expensive and what is not. The burglar will get advantage on any roll to determine the cost of a mundane (nonmagical) item of value."
                    }
                }
            }
            #t5oFeifLSTQOwHo6JVCY1GSA ^"Expert Burglar" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "After many bountiful heists, you gain enough reputation to be known as an expert burglar. You can advance into the Master level after taking at least two Expert level techniques. Each technique will cost you 200 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tMJIqdenQHW4pZhKSmoMlK87 ^"Eloquent Speech" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets a different use of this method: Duskshadow (200 PEX): The duskshadow will have advantage on Intimidation checks while on a heist. Darkblade (200 PEX): The darkblade will have advantage on Persuasion checks while on a heist. Venomtongue (200 PEX): The venomtongue will have advantage on Deception checks while on a heist."
                    }
                    #tgXsXxBT33BiZtFrOA2f0hzy ^"Resistance - Arrest" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method. The burglar has connections everywhere: the guards, the court, the jail… Everywhere. The burglar can offer bribes according to the table: Law Enforcers 50 gp; Tradespeople 100 gp; City Officials 250 gp; Arcane Personage 500 gp; Divine Personage 500 gp; High Officials 1000 gp. This ability can be used only once per heist."
                    }
                    #tfcwRH5QWWlASOTTlQ033OkG ^"Resistance - Interrogation" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method. An expert burglar knows how to resist interrogation. When resisting any kind of torture and interrogation, the burglar gets an advantage on its Constitution and Wisdom saving throws."
                    }
                    #t3FpEp73AErwzOpKh9u0J0Ub ^"Resistance - Protection" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method. An expert burglar knows how to evade protection spells. When against such magical protection, the burglar's saves will have proficiency in them."
                    }
                    #trkKit01vQCEtxOTrwv7MM1h ^"Tools of the Trade - Magical" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this method: Duskshadow (200 PEX): The Duskshadow gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Duskshadow can use it. This talisman is called The Dark Badge and can be used to reroll any Stealth roll which is not a natural 1. The user has to accept the new roll. Darkblade (200 PEX): The Darkblade gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Darkblade can use it. This talisman is called Serrated Blade. It is a short sword that you break after using it. The target needs to make a Constitution saving throw (DC 12) at the start of its round or lose 1 Hp each round after the initial damage for 1 minute and the target's movement drops to half. Venomtongue (200 PEX): The Venomtongue gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Venomtongue can use it. This talisman is called Dark Poison. It is a poison that for all intents and purposes shows the Venomtongue as if he or she is dead. After 12 hours, or the Venomtongue takes 1 damage of any kind, the Venomtongue awakens."
                    }
                    #tLaS8i9NIrlKxiDFKg1caqZ3 ^"Mock Profession" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All burglars can get this method. The burglar gains a mock profession to shield its illicit activities. You gain proficiency in a tool."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tNAdAGfkaCVvCrbnff8oncMw ^"Master Burglar" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 4
                PERKS {
                    #tTPqJOuOLbU8kH61FDzhVT9V ^"Stories of the Past" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have a lot of experiences, stories, and probably have been a part of legends and myths. You have the ability to inspire greatness in others. You can grant inspiration to anyone who listens to your stories a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus daily. This inspiration point must be used in 1 hour or lost. Anyone who already has an inspiration point won't be affected by this."
                    }
                    #tHPScT3ZSTIEKhi8YHIxNZDV ^"Leader of the Guild" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "As an established, respected member and leader of your guild, you can rely on certain benefits that your membership provides: • Your guild standing will provide you with lavish lodging and food. • The guild will pay for your resurrection if you need such a service. (You will owe a debt to the guild) • You will always have a guildhall provided to you in every city or town which has a thieves’ guild. • The Guild offers tremendous political power. If you are accused of a crime, your guild will support you no matter what. • You can get access to powerful political figures through your guild. Such connections may require donations."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    #txtGxz4YpZ10f5whfkcYLWwp ^"The Alchemist" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Profession"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "Being an Alchemist A calm and stoic life with a chance to improve yourself on a daily basis, honing your skills of making potions, elixirs, and concoctions–The hard work of an alchemist never ends."
            ^"Overview" STRING "How to Play? As an alchemist, you will need to gather ingredients for your potions; then you will need to mix them in particular ways. The goal is to sell them to your buyers, earn some money and start it from the top.

Climbing the Ranks: For each potion you create, you gain PEX (Profession Experience) and when you gather enough PEX you will advance in the ranks of alchemists. When you reach Rank 2 as an alchemist, you will have to be specialized in the way of alchemy. You earn PEX according to the potions you create. Each potion will give you different amounts of PEX according to rarities.

Cooking Potions, A General Rule Anything an alchemist creates is considered a consumable. For every day of downtime you spend crafting, you can craft one or more items with a total market value not exceeding 25 gp, and you must expend raw materials worth half the total market value. If something you want to craft has a market value greater than 25 gp, you make progress every day in 25-gp increments until you reach the market value of the item. For example, a dose of poison of adder’s bite (market value 400 gp) takes 16 days to craft by yourself.

Multiple characters can combine their efforts toward the crafting of a single item, provided that the characters all have proficiency with the requisite tools and are working together in the same place. Each character contributes 25 gp worth of effort for every day spent helping to craft the item.

While crafting, you can maintain a modest lifestyle without having to pay 1 gp per day, or a comfortable lifestyle at half the normal cost."
            ^"Aspiring Background" STRING "You decide to spend your life as an alchemist, and by taking this background, you can start this profession at level 1 with 0 PEX as an Apprentice Alchemist. Proficiencies + Equipment

Skill Proficiencies: Arcana, Nature

Languages: Any one of your choice.

Tool Proficiencies: Alchemist’s Supplies.

Equipment: Alchemist’s Supplies, a set of quality clothes, a carving knife, a scroll case full of parchment, a vial of ink, 10 gp."
        }
