        RANKS {
            #t0Vzfs6MSm6B0yXDCiWfGseT ^"Apprentice Alchemist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 1
                ^"Description"
                STRING "As an apprentice alchemist, you understand the most basic formulas and the simplest creations. In addition to picking up Tools of the Trade - Basic, you will have to choose one from the methods below:"
                PERKS {
                    #tyvUn1ulvhm4YKtQQZvuqeCj ^"Accomplished Chemist - Basic" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The alchemist gains proficiency in Alchemist's Supplies. The alchemist gains the ability to produce a basic potion of healing, vial of acid, antitoxin, lightrod, smokedust, entangling bag, and firestone.

Basic Potion of Healing: You regain hit points when you drink this potion. 2d4+2. (Price 25 gp) Potion of Climbing: When you drink this potion, you gain a climbing speed equal to your walking speed for 1 hour. During this time you have advantage on athletics checks for climbing. (Price 25 gp)

Vial of Acid: As an action you can splash the contents of this vial onto a creature within 5 feet of you or throw the vial up to 20 feet, shattering it on impact. In either case, make a ranged attack against a creature or object, treating acid as an improvised weapon. On a hit, the target takes 2d6 acid damage. (Price 25 gp)

Antitoxin: A creature that drinks this vial of liquid gains advantage on saving throws against poison for 1 hour. It confers no benefit to undead or constructs. (Price 25 gp)

Lightrod: A lightrod is an alchemically enchanted rod. As an action, you can use it to illuminate an area much like the light cantrip. (Price 5 gp)

Smokedust: As an action, you can ignite this alchemically created dust (usually in a pouch) and throw it up to 30 feet. Thich smoke emerges from the pouch, producing an effect much like fog cloud spell. The area of effect for this is a 10-foot sphere, and the duration is five minutes. (Price 20 gp)

Entangling Bag: This fragile cloth sack contains a goo that expands when it comes into contact with air. As an action you can throw the bag up to 30 feet, causing an effect much like the web spell (DC 12), but it only affects a 5-foot cube area, and the duration is 5 minutes. The entangling bag has no effect on creatures larger than Large size, incorporeal, and oozes. (Price 25 gp)

Firestone: When this bright crystal strikes a hard surface, it blows up with a very loud bang that can be heard from a mile away, and both blinds and deafens nearby creatures. As an action, you can throw the stone at a hard surface within 30 feet. Any creature within 10 feet of that point is affected by a blindness/deafness spell (DC 12), causing blindness or deafness effect. (Price 25 gp)"
                    }
                    #tVY4QJBonbPkmld10fXUHjoT ^"Discern Ingredients" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The alchemist always knows what ingredients to use for potions and has an eye open for such components during travel and encounters. The GM has to work with the alchemist to provide information on special ingredients. Each ingredient can be used once per potion, and it will decrease the cost by 10%."
                    }
                    #tlXeVSCSFEjZoSwt7gdtEWHc ^"Proper Mixing Technique" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The alchemist knows how to mix the potions properly and how to benefit from certain special tricks by doing so. The preparation time of any potion the alchemist creates will decrease by 20%."
                    }
                    #tGxJo6InyyaH8p6fsAEvL50o ^"Professional Interest" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The alchemist gains proficiency in Alchemist's Supplies. The alchemist gains the ability to produce a basic potion of healing, vial of acid, antitoxin, lightrod, smokedust, entangling bag, and firestone."
                    }
                }
            }
            #texcTtsJrIS2ThpUQrMeKmUY ^"Journeyman Alchemist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(300 PEX) You are now a journeyman alchemist and have intensive knowledge about what you can create. Now you have a specialty, and in that specialty, you will have an edge.

You can advance into the Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level methods. Each method will cost you 100 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tbXj7eD0op0J8G703PhkW6Ji ^"Specialization Choice:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have to choose one of the two specialization choices: Poison Master who specializes in creating poisons, or the Elixir Master who specializes in creating oils and potions."
                    }
                    #tJpvVbepg9y5hTznK4Dnvpm2 ^"Extensive Extract Knowledge I" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this technique:

Poison Master: The poison master will learn to produce the following:

The Bat: (Inhaled) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 13) or become poisoned for 1 hour. The poisoned creature is also blinded. (Price 250 gp)

Slumber: (Injury) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 12) or be poisoned for 1 hour. The poisoned creature is also knocked unconscious. The creature will wake up if damaged in any way or another creature can use an action to wake it up. (Price 250 gp)

Unwaver: (Ingested) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw(DC 12) or become poisoned for 1 hour. The poisoned creature can’t tell lies while under the effect of this poison. (Price 150 gp)

Elixir Master (100 PEX): Elixir Master will learn to produce the following:

Fauna Affection: When you drink this potion, you are under the effect of an animal friendship spell (DC 13) for 1 hour. (Price 150 gp)

Strong Lungs: When you drink this potion, you can breathe underwater for 1 hour.

The Heart: The next time you see a creature within 10 minutes after drinking this elixir, you become charmed by that creature for 1 hour. If the creature is of a species and gender you are normally attracted to, you regard it as your true love while you are charmed."
                    }
                    #t8Y2sck8C8yFFSca7rEkZG6g ^"Extensive Extract Knowledge II" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Extensive Liquid Knowledge I needs to be purchased before this. Each specialty gets a different use of this technique:

Poison Master: The poison master will learn to produce the following:

Adder Bite: (Injury) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 11) or take 10 (3d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. (Price 200 gp)

Ghoul’s Touch: (Contact) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 13) or become poisoned for 3d6 hours. The poisoned creature is paralyzed. (Price 400 gp)

Burned Gangar Root: (Inhaled) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 12) or take 10 (3d6) poison damage and must repeat the saving throw at the start of each of its turns. On each successive failed saves, the creature takes 3 (1d6) more poison damage. After three successful saves, the effect of the poison ends. (Price 450 gp)

Vile Curse: A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 15) or take 3 (1d6) poison damage and become poisoned. The poisoned creature must repeat the saving throw every day, taking 3 (1d6) poison damage on a failed save. Until the effects of this poison end, the damage the poison inflicts can’t be healed by any means. After seven successful saving throws, the effect ends, and the creature can heal normally. (Price 200 gp)

Elixir Master (100 PEX): Elixir Master will learn to produce the following:

Slick Slack: The oil can cover a medium or smaller creature, along with any equipment worn or carried. Applying the oil takes 10 minutes. The affected creature gains the effect of freedom of movement spell for 8 hours. (Price 250 gp)

Embiggen: When you drink this potion, you gain the “enlarge” effect of the enlarge/reduce spell for 1d6 hours. (Price 150 gp)

Basic Behemoth's Edge: When you drink this potion, your Strength score changes to 21 for 1 hour. This potion has no effect if your strength is already 21 or higher. (Price 450 gp)

Potion of Greater Healing: You regain hit points when you drink this potion. 4d4+4. (Price 250 gp)"
                    }
                    #tns5BD6yrvx5FH7wgRd2B9X9 ^"Extensive Extract Knowledge III" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Extensive Liquid Knowledge I and II need to be purchased before this. Each specialty gets a different use of this technique:

Poison Master: The poison master will learn to produce the following:

Vile Bile: (Contact) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 12) or be poisoned for 1 minute. The poisoned creature is also paralyzed. (Price 150 gp)

Corrosive Vitae: (Ingested) A creature subjected to this poison must make a Constitution saving throw (DC 11). The creature takes 6 (1d12) poison damage and is poisoned for 24 hours. On a successful save, the creature takes half the damage and isn’t poisoned. (150 gp)

Anesthetic Essence: (Inhaled) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 14) or become poisoned for 8 hours. The poisoned creature is also unconscious. The creature will wake up if damaged in any way or another creature can use an action to wake it up. (250 gp)

Komodo Bite: (Injury) A creature subjected to this poison must make a Constitution saving throw (DC 14) or take 18 (6d6) poison damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful save. (1000 gp)

Elixir Master (100 PEX): Elixir Master will learn to produce the following:

Sight Beyond Sight: When you drink this potion, you gain the effect of the clairvoyance spell. (300 gp)

Shrinking: When you drink this potion, you gain the “reduce” effect of the enlarge/reduce spell for 1d4 hours. (150 gp)

Potion of Superior Healing: You regain hit points when you drink this potion. 8d4+8. (Price 1250 gp)

Advanced Behemoth's Edge: When you drink this potion, your Strength score changes to 23 for 1 hour. This potion has no effect if your strength is already 23 or higher. (Price 2500 gp)"
                    }
                }
            }
            #tOMnQdaAR9CrcH1rU0dzTTTU ^"Expert Alchemist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(1000 PEX) After years of training and producing potion after potion, you came to be known as an expert alchemist.

You can advance into the Master level after taking at least two Expert level methods. Each method will cost you 200 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tyPXI1zrzcdgz3UrtrDqjike ^"Extensive Extract Knowledge IV" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Extensive Liquid Knowledge I, II, and III needs to be purchased before this. Each specialty gets different use of this technique:

Poison Master (200 PEX): The poison master will learn to produce the following:

The Day’s End: (Ingested) A creature that ingests this poison suffers no effect until the day ends. If the poison has not been neutralized before then, the creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 16), taking 27 (9d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful save. (1250 gp)

Black Grease: (Contact) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 18) or become poisoned for 24 hours. The poisoned creature is unconscious. The creature wakes up if it is damaged in some way. (Price 350 gp)

Demonic Corroder: (Injury) A creature subjected to this poison must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 19) taking 42 (14d6) poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful save. (Price 2500 gp)

Elixir Master (200 PEX): Elixir Master will learn to produce the following:

Expert Behemoth's Edge: When you drink this potion, your Strength score changes to 25 for 1 hour. This potion has no effect if your strength is already 25 or higher. (Price 3500 gp)

Ghostly Pallor: The oil can cover a Medium or smaller creature, along with any equipment worn or carried. Applying the oil takes 10 minutes. The affected creature gains the effect of the etherealness spell for 1 hour. (Price 1250 gp)

Puff of Smoke: When you drink this potion, you will gain the benefit of a gaseous form spell for 1 hour. (Price 550 gp)"
                    }
                    #tQjbkW4oBxilx63pepk2rpg4 ^"Garish Resistance Potions" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Both specialization choices can take this. After years of practice and study, you start to produce potions of Psychic, Thunder, and Lightning Resistance. (Price 350 each)"
                    }
                    #tad3FYbHxD8wg259EwOvaysw ^"Horrid Resistance Potions" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Both specialization choices can take this. After years of practice and study, you start to produce potions of Acid, Poison, and Necrotic Resistance. (Price 350 each)"
                    }
                    #t03dwJOCI4KiU3pQflSfXFVm ^"Environmental Resistance Potions" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Both specialization choices can take this. Resistance II needs to be purchased before taking this, however. After years of practice and study, you start to produce potions of Cold, Fire, Force, and Radiant Resistance. (Price 350 each)"
                    }
                    #tr8Ol8jZfpB9h5kU9U3WkgAh ^"Tools of the Trade - Advanced" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The alchemist, after years of trial and error, gains the best equipment there is on the market for producing alchemical concoctions. The alchemist gains expertise in the use of alchemist’s supplies."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tPhDNVkIyjvyoNGFqhU5BEK4 ^"Master Alchemist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 4
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(5000 PEX)

Alchemist Downtime Activities

Insignificant Experimentation: You either go on sabbatical or go awol to work on your ingredients and potions. Choose one: Earn 10 gold, or spend 20 gold and earn 20 PEX.

Decent Experimentation: You decide to work on bigger, more complex projects, choose one: Earn 15 gold, or spend 30 gold and earn 35 PEX.

Considerable Experimentation: You work on a more serious, more complex project and work on it for three weeks, most probably working together with a few of your colleagues. Choose one: Earn 25 gold, or spend 50 gold and earn 50 PEX.

Glorious Experimentation: You work among the best alchemists in the realms, spending a month of time and benefit from their experiences. Choose one: Earn 50 gold, or spend 100 gold and earn 120 PEX.

ALCHEMIST MAGNUM OPUS QUEST

The Magnum Opus Quest should be accessible only to the most accomplished and capable of the alchemists. While preparing a Magnum Opus Quest for the alchemist, the GM needs to prepare this quest according to the motivations of the alchemist. The alchemist needs to have a proper purpose for embarking on this quest. Personal Reason (Roll d8): 1 Old Age–old age is a great motivation for a person to prolong life; 2 For the sake of a cherished persona; 3 To prove that they are worthy of a cause; 4 To weed out among the ranks of an organization; 5 To gain fame, fortune, and glory; 6 For the sake of academic research and advancement; 7 For the sake of uncovering the secrets of the universe and sharing them; 8 For the sake of earning more wisdom, knowledge, or power.

There are four steps to prepare the Magnum Opus Quest for an alchemist character:

Step One, Acquire the Recipe: The recipe is the most important part of a legendary potion, so we have to decide how the alchemist character achieves this recipe. Event (Roll d6): 1 The recipe was lost in the ancient textbooks, divided into different owners; 2 The recipe is among the hoard of a powerful entity or a creature; 3 The recipe is hidden by the alchemists of the old in an intricate puzzle; 4 The recipe never worked correctly in the past, but it is common knowledge; 5 Some powerful authority figure owns the recipe; 6 The recipe is a gift or blessing from a deity. Acquiring the recipe should be a fun adventure as collecting the necessary ingredients to prepare the potion.

Step Two, Acquiring the Ingredients: Every recipe has many ingredients, these three tables will give some ideas to the Dungeon Master to decide on how to determine random ingredients for the potion. Common Ingredient (Roll d20): 1 Mandrake Root; 2 Mammoth Tusk; 3 Moth Dust; 4 Griffon Tailfeather; 5 Newt Eye; 6 Ostrich Eggshell; 7 Watermelon Seeds; 8 Cat’s Tail; 9 Silver Dust; 10 Mistletoe Seeds; 11 Charcoal Dust; 12 Sesame Seed Oil; 13 Ant Venom; 14 Royal Jelly; 15 Giant Lizard Scales; 16 Pure Water; 17 Blessed Salt; 18 Sweet Bergamot; 19 Grave Dust; 20 Levander Oil. Uncommon Ingredient (Roll d20): 1 Elven Tears; 2 Pure Lead; 3 Grounded Undead Bones; 4 Giant Ant Antenna; 5 Kobold Milk; 6 Nightshade; 7 Goblin Ear; 8 Lightning Struck Tree Bark; 9 Giant Scorpion Stinger; 10 Red Amanita Mushroom; 11 Monitor Lizard Scales; 12 Pure Alcohol; 13 Blessed Water; 14 Giant Butterfly Dust; 15 Giant Toad Venom; 16 Troll Eyes; 17 Blood Lichen; 18 Morning Dew; 19 Wolfsbane; 20 Premium Dwarven Ale. Rare Ingredient (Roll d20): 1 Basilisk Eye; 2 Ghost Ectoplasm; 3 Grounded Devil Bone; 4 Cyclops Eye; 5 Chimera Dragon Scale; 6 Elemental Core (d4 1 Earth 2 Fire 3 Water 4 Air); 7 Celestial Feather; 8 Hell Hound Saliva; 9 Golem’s Essence (d4 1 Clay 2 Flesh, 3 Stone 4 Iron); 10 Medusa Hair Snake; 11 Werebeast’s Fur (d10 1-2 Rat, 3-4 Boar 5-6 Bear 7-8 Wold 9-10 Tiger); 12 Purpleworm Blood; 13 Dryad’s Tears; 14 Mephit Essence (d4 1 Dust 2 Ice 3 Magma 4 Steam); 15 Aboleth Skin; 16 Giant’s Beard (d6 1 Hill 2 Frost 3 Stone 4 Fire 5 Cloud 6 Storm); 17 Satyr’s Horns; 18 Ettin Tusks (d6 1-2 Left Head 3-4 Right Head 5-6 All); 19 Manticore Tail Spike; 20 Al Ghaib Essence from a captured Djinn. Very Rare Ingredient (Roll d20): 1 Skin from a Doppelganger, Flayed while Alive; 2 Cauldron from a Coven of Hags, Forcefully Taken; 3 Wrappings from a Mummy Lord, Forcefully Taken; 4 Essence of a Deity, Forcefully Taken; 5 Poison from a Guardian Naga, Willingly Given; 6 Blood of a Fallen Angel, Forcefully Taken; 7 Heartblood of a True Dragon, Willingly Given; 8 Wingfeather from a Pegasus, Willingly Given; 9 Fur from a Rakshasa, Skinned while Alive; 10 Tongue from a Hydra, Cut while Alive; 11 Talon from a Roc, Forcefully Taken; 12 Hair from a Sphinx, Willingly Given; 13 Tentacle from a Kraken, Forcefully Taken; 14 Tail from a Succubus/Incubus, Cut while Alive (d4 1-2 Succubus 3-4 Incubus); 15 Ink from a Kraken, Forcefully Taken; 16 Tail Scale from a Dragon Turtle, Swiped while Asleep; 17 Horn of the Unicorn, Forcefully Taken; 18 Bloof of an Elder Vampire, Forcefully Taken; 19 Stingervenom from a Pseudodragon, Willingly Given; 20 Essence of a Will-O’-Wisp, Forcefully Taken. The GM can roll any number of times from any number of tables according to the recipe.

Step Three, Cooking the Potion: The alchemist knows the recipe, the ingredients are ready–now it is time to prepare the potion. The alchemist needs to use a specific tool to mix and transmogrify the potion, use a specific mixing method to prepare it, and specialized tools to preserve it. Roll d6 & d6 & d6 — Mixing Tool / Mixing Method / Preservation Method and Tool: 1 Golden Ladle / Boiling / Special Alloy Cauldron; 2 Crystal Spoon / Distilling / Specialized Alchemy Set; 3 Lead Bar / Freezing / Arcane Laboratory; 4 Steel Fork / Deaeration / Pressurized Chambers; 5 Cured Bark / Infusion / Environmental Infusion; 6 Charcoal Stick / Blessing / Another Plane of Existence. This process should take weeks and maybe months, and each day the alchemist must invest at least 8 hours into preparing this potion.

Step Four, Battling the Side Effects: The potion is ready, but it will be hard for the alchemist to resist the side effects and battle against them. Roll d6 — Save / Side Effect: 1 Strength / Alchemist is petrified into stone for 24 hours; 2 Dexterity / Alchemist’s speed is reduced to half; 3 Constitution / Alchemist’s eyes become sensitive to sunlight; 4 Intelligence / Alchemist becomes narcoleptic; 5 Wisdom / Alchemist loses the ability to lie and deceive; 6 Charisma / Alchemist’s tongue becomes numb, losing the ability to speak. The GM can use any of the effects above for any amount of time. The saving throws should be rolled daily, and the duration of each effect shouldn’t be less than a week.

Lastly, The Reward: After this exhausting process, the alchemist should have a fitting reward. We would like to give one special ability as a reward, but the GM can give any other reward other than this.

Everliving: The alchemist stops aging. The alchemist gains immunity to any ability and age-draining effect from any source. Also, the alchemist gains poison and acid resistance."
                PERKS {
                    #tDiMBG1DgCuUMGQJeZ5wQyk1 ^"Stories of the Past:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have a lot of experiences, stories, and have probably taken part in some of the legends and myths. You have the ability to inspire greatness in others. You can grant inspiration to anyone who listens to your stories a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus daily. This inspiration point must be used in 1 hour or it will be lost. Anyone who already has an inspiration point won't be affected by this."
                    }
                    #tTJI7KuIKIZj2spk8UyeokYs ^"Alchemist Extraordinaire:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "With the use of proper techniques and an expert understanding, the alchemist prepares better potions now. The alchemist gains the ability to prepare very rare potions but finding proper recipes for them will be another adventure."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    #tIOMDJpM9xXLjKSEmGVGG8uo ^"The Antiquarian" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Profession"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "Being an Antiquarian The life of a scientist who is versed in folklore and legends is never easy. Being a historian, a collector and an arcane researcher is both fulfilling and fruitful. The joy of providing prosperity with actual information about the properties of magic, wonders of enchanted items, and the vast world of magical research is, in itself, a very fulfilling job."
            ^"Overview" STRING "How to Play? Find a dungeon, gather magical objects and non-magical historical objects, and present them to your colleagues in the academy or the occult circles. Write papers, books, and articles about ancient cultures, foreign languages, wonders of magic, and items of power.

Climbing the Ranks For each magical item you discover from old ruins, dungeons, or lost cities, you will gain PEX (Profession Experience) and when you gather enough PEX, you will advance in the ranks of the antiquarians. When you reach Rank 2 as an antiquarian you will have to be specialized in one way of an antiquarian."
            ^"Aspiring Background" STRING "You decide to spend your life as an antiquarian and by taking this background you can start this profession at level 1 with 0 PEX as an Apprentice Antiquarian. Proficiencies + Equipment

Skill Proficiencies: Arcana, History

Languages: Any two of your choice.

Tool Proficiencies: None.

Equipment: A book scribbled with notes, a bottle of ink, an ink pen, traveler's clothes, a pouch containing 10 gp."
        }
