            #t3H7kh1zSxsKGRXsy5ijwtmf ^"Journeyman Antiquarian" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "You are now a journeyman antiquarian and uncovered plenty of artifacts with historical value, many items of magical power, and copious secrets of importance. Now you have a specialty and in that specialty, you will have an edge.

You can advance into the Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level innovations. Each innovation will cost you 100 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tmUEXTu7LUVUphUt0p4zgrvS ^"Specialization Choice:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have to choose one of the two specialization choices: A Historian who specializes in discovering historical facts, and an Arcanist who specializes in discovering magical facts."
                    }
                    #tDGSrLVbGwnDpk9M3ORFwcHg ^"Accomplished Investigator" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this innovation:

Historian: After spending 8 hours in some kind of research facility, such as a library, the Historian gains advantage on any History check. If the Historian already has advantage on Intelligence (History) checks, he gains expertise.

Arcanist: After spending 8 hours in some kind of an arcane research facility such as a magic institute, the Arcanist gains advantage on any Intelligence (Arcana) check. If the Arcanist already has advantage on Arcana checks, he gains expertise.

Antiquarians gather in academies and guilds, when they are around each other they tend to speak about their experiences, their discoveries, and the knowledge they amassed in their travels. The antiquarian will have access to such places and will have a chance to do research and investigation."
                    }
                    #tZocaDzUT7t2I0LJTvZfPi8A ^"Proper Thaumaturgy" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The antiquarian knows how to use consumable items such as scrolls better than everyone else. When you use such an item to cast a spell, you have a chance to keep the last charge of it from being expended. You will have to roll Arcana according to the following DCs: Common Scroll 15, Uncommon Scroll 20, Rare Scroll 25, Very Rare 30."
                    }
                    #tlhtfZJjo9rLQ6HrcCcEAn3R ^"Tools of the Trade - Advanced" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The antiquarian gains more experience with the use of the tools of his art. The antiquarian chooses any one tool proficiency and gains proficiency in it. The antiquarian needs to only work for 125 days and pay 125 gp for this."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tgS12As2zX34OtDbhd3g8bRk ^"Expert Antiquarian" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(1000 PEX) You are now an expert antiquarian with many years of research, many papers published in many academies, and have amassed a great deal of historical or arcane knowledge.

You can advance into the Master level after taking at least two Expert level innovations. Each innovation will cost you 200 PEX."
                PERKS {
