        RANKS {
            #tcOVoMlmHh3Sc2YGw5bo7W6X ^"Apprentice Archelogist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 1
                ^"Description"
                STRING "As an apprentice archeologist, you understand the basics of your profession and you know the basic preservation crafts, you will have to choose one from the below:

You can advance into the Journeyman level after taking at least two Apprentice level preservation crafts. Each preservation craft will cost you 50 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #thSuHRPglrYiFA4cWFMjuTAC ^"Tools of the Trade - Protective Gear" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "As an explorer, you will have to get accustomed to any harsh environment and weather conditions. In time the protective gear you wear will be specialized and help you in many different conditions. You will be immune to any non-magical heat or cold damage caused by weather conditions, and also your movement speed will be less hindered by difficult terrain: the first 10 feet of any difficult terrain will not hinder you at all during combat."
                    }
                    #ts7etsS6TtyCkOsKZjHBHY2a ^"Tools of the Trade - Expert Tools" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "As an archeologist, you will need to survive in any derelict and sometimes need to gain access to closed doors. You become proficient in Dungeoneer's Kits and Thieves Tools."
                    }
                    #txbVAbczj4tDvOlQR1fHIENn ^"Internal Compass" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You never lose your way or direction due to your internal compass. You get advantage on Intelligence (Investigation) or Wisdom (Survival) checks to determine your way when looking for directions."
                    }
                    #tmIxeYQQUYGZMmfxyMFU8JZQ ^"Eye for Value" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The archeologist needs to have a trained eye to see what is a valuable relic and what is not. The archeologist will get an advantage on any roll to determine the rarity of a mundane (nonmagical) item of value."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tME79GU0Wm5BqvTaWwYxTVKU ^"Journeyman Archeologist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(300 PEX) You are now a journeyman archeologist and have some experience after restoring many relics and some derelicts for prosperity. Now you will have a specialty and in this specialty, you will have an edge.

You can advance into the Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level preservation crafts. Each preservation craft will cost you 100 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tfvCZ6Sd3Fux61Xl1u9FHDiK ^"Specialization Choice:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You will have to choose one of the two: An Explorer is always on the road to find more places to explore and restore, and The Preserver is more specialized in preserving the buildings of old and restoring them for the next generation to cherish."
                    }
                    #tnFA11KFm2w2BQ5AFaYfjcc7 ^"Craft Know-how" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets a different use of this preservation craft:

Explorer: The Explorer is adept at finding, retrieving, and restoring relics. When you restore a relic as an explorer, you gain an extra 1 PEX.

Preserver: The Preserver is the master at restoring, cleaning, and repairing derelicts and ruins. When you restore a relic as a preserver, you gain 20% more PEX (round up)."
                    }
                    #tFvSdoFTjIcrOjoqcJdfdckh ^"Tools of the Trade - Elevational Gear" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All archeologists can get this preservation craft. The archeologists will always benefit from grappling hooks and whips. You gain proficiency with the whip, regardless of your martial weapon training. Also, any climbing attempt with a grappling hook will always have advantage."
                    }
                    #tZoBvN63hlfud4oiVYoOf18D ^"Tricks of the Trade - Minor Magics" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All Archeologists can get this preservation craft. You learn the prestidigitation cantrip, which doesn't count against the number of cantrips you know."
                    }
                    #tePT0nm1dUD8dr5p7ETvmkMh ^"Lore of the Past" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All archeologists can get this preservation craft. You will gain advantage in any Intelligence (History) checks to remember any facts about the culture that the relic or the derelict you are working on at the moment."
                    }
                }
            }
            #trskeSPiO8zoULmFTouKMGuf ^"Expert Archeologist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(1000 PEX) After many derelicts and relics are restored, you gain enough skill and fame to be known as an expert archeologist.

You can advance into the Master level after taking at least two Expert level preservation crafts. Each preservation craft will cost you 200 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #t80OWJpKnI64iN6tptvljgCz ^"Expert Knowledge" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each Specialty gets different use of this preservation craft:

Explorer: You learn the alarm spell as a ritual only, which doesn't count against the number of spells you know.

Preserver: You learn the comprehend languages spell as a ritual only, which doesn't count against the number of spells you know."
                    }
                    #tQtSNBIPkMlmtSHN75P9zNWW ^"Adept Linguist" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All archeologists can get this preservation craft. You will gain a language of your choice. You will be able to read, write and speak this language, even if it is a dead one."
                    }
                    #tDubKVeLI3LNRmNGimc3UauQ ^"Attention to Detail" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All archeologists can get this preservation craft. You will have advantage on any Wisdom (Perception) checks made to observe the details of a relic or a derelict."
                    }
                    #tcVQrkOJwOHukEPwdPF0698Z ^"Tools of the Trade - Magical" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this preservation craft:

Explorer: The Explorer gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Explorer can use it. This talisman is called Whispers of the Ancient and can be used to communicate with a non-hostile, non-corporeal being for 1 hour.

Preserver: The Preserver gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Preserver can use it. This talisman is called Mending Glue and can be used to clean corrosion off metal or rot off the wood. Also, it can be used to fix stone. Each use of Mending Glue can affect 1 cubic foot."
                    }
                    #tNggOQGIVCvcWmnMiQij5Rij ^"Analytical Thinking" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All archeologists can get this preservation craft. The archeologist has an educated and quick mind. Any Intelligence checks made to understand the workings of a relic or details of the derelict are made with advantage."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tlKQU7gKea65e3NCShQviTjP ^"Master Archeologist" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 4
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(5000 PEX)"
                PERKS {
                    #tOqdOdnidx1JLccPPLJiT7rx ^"Stories of the Past:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have a lot of experiences, stories, and probably have been a part of legends and myths. You have the ability to inspire greatness in others. You can grant inspiration to anyone who listens to your stories a number of times up to your proficiency bonus daily. This inspiration point must be used in 1 hour or lost. Anyone who already has an inspiration point won't be affected by this."
                    }
                    #tsdvDQt1iMMiygyv7MoNTdso ^"Museum Master:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "As an esteemed, honored member and headmaster of the Archeologists Association, you can rely on certain benefits that your membership provides:

• The Association will provide you with lavish lodging options
• The Association will provide mundane transportation methods for any dig or investigation you are part of as long as the grant is not abused in any way
• You will have allies, contacts, and esteemed colleagues in every city or town where an Archeologists Association has a base of operations, a learning institution such as a university, or a museum."
                    }
                    #tnSRxNYVKl9wa9izoLXne5K0 ^"Archeologist Downtime Activities" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Insignificant Dig: You go on a small dig or a search for a relic of small importance for one week, and at the end, choose one: Earn 10 gold, or spend 20 gold and earn 20 PEX.

Decent Dig: You go on a slightly bigger dig or go search for a more important relic for ten days, and at the end, choose one: Earn 15 gold, or spend 30 gold and earn 35 PEX.

Considerable Dig: You go on a larger scale dig or go search for a larger scale relic for three weeks, probably joining a larger party of 10+ Archeologists, learning valuable lessons on your trade. Choose one: Earn 25 gold, or spend 50 gold and earn 50 PEX.

Glorious Dig: You go on a very large dig or go search for a very large scale relic hunt for one month, working with the best of the best, going after either very important places or relics which are connected to each other, earning grandiose amounts of experience. Choose one: Earn 50 gold, or spend 100 gold and earn 120 PEX."
                    }
                    #tMP3WoFHMhZBFURH22Cj5Cn5 ^"Archeologist Magnum Opus Quest" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The Magnum Opus Quest should be embarked only by the most esteemed and respected archeologists, and any inexperienced archeologist should wait for their time to come. While preparing a Magnum Opus for the archeologist, the GM needs to prepare a reason for the archeologist to go on this once in a lifetime dig. The most justifiable choice in this is to give the character a personal reason to search for such a relic or a derelict. The table below can give some ideas to answer to this question:

Personal Reason (d8):
1. The uncovered relic/derelict will answer an important question on a lost culture
2. The uncovered relic/derelict will answer the secrets of the universe
3. For the sake of academic research and advancement.
4. To serve a higher cause.
5. To weed out among the ranks of Archeologists Association.
6. The uncovered relic/derelict will provide wisdom, knowledge, or power.
7. Just for the sake of it.
8. To gain fortune and fame by uncovering this relic/derelict.

There are four steps to prepare the Magnum Opus Quest for an archeologist character.

Step One, Creating the Backstory: The legendary relic or derelict the archeologist is after should have an intricate and alluring story. The table below can give some ideas to the GM to decide on how to lead the archeologist throughout this adventure:
Event (d6):
1. The relic or derelict is inherited from an archaic spellcaster of an old era.
2. The exact location of the relic or derelict is known but it is a hard-to-reach position.
3. The final resting place of the relic or derelict is unknown but it can be tracked in different places.
4. The relic or derelict is filled with traps (or protected by traps) and nobody yet has returned alive from a dig.
5. To find this relic or derelict a specific trail full of puzzles needs to be followed.
6. The relic or derelict is said to be gifted to mortals as a blessing.
The legendary relic or derelict needs to have a lavishly spun legend surrounding it.

Step Two, Deciding on the Journey: The relic or derelict is far away from culture and needs to be reached before any dig or research can be made; this journey should be a grand adventure. The table below can give some ideas to the GM to decide on how to lead the archeologist throughout this journey:
Vehicle (d6):
1. A Sailing Vessel
2. A Horsecart
3. On Foot
4. A Flying Vessel
5. A Train
6. Magical Transportation
The GM should give delicious bits of information during the journey and keep the character interested in the journey.

Step Three, Determining the Importance: We know where the relic or derelict is and we need to give the character a specific sense of importance. The table below can give some ideas to the GM to decide on how to lead the archeologist throughout this journey:
Importance of the Dig (d6):
1. The derelict or relic is from a long-lost culture.
2. The research made on the derelict or relic will advance known science.
3. Some lost magical secret is embedded into the derelict or the relic.
4. The derelict or the relic tells of an apocalyptic prophecy.
5. The derelict or the relic holds to salvation from a grand problem.
6. The derelict or the relic is a religious artifact that will shed light into a distant past.
The GM should give some detail into showing the importance of the relic or the derelict to the character.

Step Four, Choose the Future: The story of the relic or the derelict almost comes to an end; all there is missing is what this important piece of history is going to become. The table below can give some ideas to the GM to decide on how to conclude this long and arduous journey:
Future of the Dig (d6):
1. The contents of the dig are stored in a dark warehouse never to be seen again.
2. The contents of the dig are destroyed and forgotten.
3. The contents of the dig are restored into their former glory and are now revered by many generations.
4. The contents of the dig are considered holy ground and visited by countless pilgrims.
5. The contents of the dig are revealed to be apocalyptic and kept under guard.
6. The contents of the dig bring back a race or a culture into existence.

Lastly, The Reward: After all these long years of digs and research, the archeologist should get a great reward. We would like to give one special ability as a reward, but the GM can give any other reward than this.

Cradle of the Legends: Cradle of the Legends lets the archeologist use the legend lore spell once a day without needing material components. Also, whenever the archeologist makes an Intelligence (History) check and rolls anything below 9, it will be counted as 10."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    #tcfbriYQtUQHZzRFjpxsOGHO ^"The Spy" DEF {
        EXTENDS ^"Profession"
        PROPERTIES {
            ^"Description" STRING "Learn, whisper, and get paid. These souls of intrigue and espionage work on the act of obtaining confidential secrets from documents, people, or their very eyes. The work of a spy is usually part of larger institutions and governments, and it is through feeding secret information to their handler that they rise in their chosen career."
            ^"Overview" STRING "Infiltrate and sneak behind the enemy lines and get a hold of their secrets; then sell it to your enemies, or to the highest bidder; or rather you can work for a patron to serve under a great cause to save a nation from the oppressing forces. In your trade, the tastiest commodities are knowledge and secrets. For each secret you uncover and turn into some kind of profit, you gain PEX and advance in the ranks of spies. When you reach Rank 2 as a spy, you will have to be specialized in one way or agent craft. You earn PEX according to the secrets you uncover and deliver. The GM is the final judge on the rarity of the secrets you uncover."
            ^"Aspiring Background" STRING "You decide to spend your life as a spy and by taking this background you can start this profession at level 1 with 0 PEX as an Apprentice Spy.

Proficiencies + Equipment

Skill Proficiencies: Choose two from among Deception, Insight, Persuasion and Stealth.

Languages: Any one of your choice.

Tool Proficiencies: Any one of your choice.

Equipment: A few sets of clothes appropriate to your duties and a pouch containing 25 gp."
        }
        PEX_TABLE {
            #tOyhNYTGrcUV3Z9hjE76pLzi ^"The Spy — CR Trivial Secret" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "Trivial Secret"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 1
            }
            #tv3YsWzsfDxxAye8qVnmveOo ^"The Spy — CR Minor Secret" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "Minor Secret"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 5
            }
            #twXSHuNwNFkGKboVC0AHWyZ4 ^"The Spy — CR Important Secret" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "Important Secret"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 10
            }
            #tydfqQKzk6XwPEAC12oggPEn ^"The Spy — CR Major Secret" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "Major Secret"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 25
            }
            #th1T2kQR7v6pkY1fdTw0NEwg ^"The Spy — CR Grand Secret" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"PEX Award"
                ^"Challenge Rating"
                STRING "Grand Secret"
                ^"PEX"
                INTEGER 100
            }
        }
        RANKS {
            #tR8l8s3EIhdeJ1V8wgwBrNq0 ^"Apprentice Spy" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 1
                ^"Description"
                STRING "As an apprentice spy, you know the basics of your profession, and you know the simplest of the modus operandi; you will have to choose one from the below;

You can advance into the Journeyman level after taking at least two Apprentice level spycraft. Each spycraft will cost you 50 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tvvnRASxLd5dmyOmVpLrMGy9 ^"Skeleton Key Procurement" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "The spy always needs to be prepared for breaking and entering into some important place stealthily. You gain proficiency in the use of Thieves’ Tools."
                    }
                    #tTVNQ593grXdh2ogZJfHPiNL ^"Quick to Observe" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "A spy needs to see every detail at lightning speed. The use of the Wisdom (Perception) skill, even during combat, is a reaction for you. You don’t need to use your action or bonus action to see into details, and your eyes are well trained to perceive your surroundings hastily."
                    }
                    #txBSmGM7lvhNMzHolFTKOevf ^"Dressed for Success" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 50
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "A spy always has disguises ready for any event or situation. You gain proficiency in Disguise Kits."
                    }
                    #tTrdcWJFoyJ0YkSRh5BxFN6y ^"Blend In" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "A spy always has an edge language-wise. You will gain a language of your choice. You will be able to read, write, and speak one other language, but it can’t be a dead one."
                    }
                }
            }
            #t5bOpsImVDDC3wDJXVBuFLE6 ^"Journeyman Spy" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 2
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(300 PEX) You are now a journeyman spy and have undergone rigorous training in the art of spycraft. Now you have a specialty, and in this specialty, you will have an edge.

You can advance into the Expert level after taking at least two Journeyman level spycraft. Each spycraft will cost you 100 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tqHQLFm7j2QoxlYUP8mOEi9M ^"Specialization Choice:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have to choose one of the two: An Agent of the Government works for a higher cause to fight against their enemies. A Free Agent works for anyone who offers them a job to use their skills."
                    }
                    #tUqdvc3jpvJtX5KglbgGkubg ^"Contacts in High Places" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this spycraft:

Agent of the Government: An Agent of the Government has noble and merchant contacts all around the city; dealing and acquiring information from them will be both easier and cheaper. Any Charisma (Persuasion) check against such people will be done with advantage.

Free Agent: A Free Agent has contacts from criminal, pirate, and guard circles all around the city;dealing and acquiring information from them will be both easier and cheaper. Any Charisma (Persuasion) check against such people will be done with advantage."
                    }
                    #t3UwEIWzFIbiPZyvMT5MQxnv ^"Tools of the Trade - Well Equipped" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All spies can get this spycraft. You can show your agent badge to any quartermaster loyal to the cause you work in and get free equipment from them. You can get any common item (including magical ones) that the GM allows as long as you can justify a reason for having them. Abusing the use of this will get the agent banned for life from all such establishments."
                    }
                    #tPI8S5ah8PngqrmegvpaRfK7 ^"Accomplished Traveler" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All spies can get this spycraft. All spies should know how to move quickly in all conditions. Any movement speed you have now has a +10 bonus to it. This includes the vehicles you drive, flying, swimming, and climbing."
                    }
                    #ttBsWUx8sWxRiuJMAcm8VN3w ^"People Reader" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 100
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All spies can get this spycraft. A spy is trained to be the master of all initiation. The agent gets advantage in any Wisdom (Insight) check when people try to deceive an agent."
                    }
                }
            }
            #tosUIOC1kZu1x00uAX49FC5z ^"Expert Spy" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 3
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(1000 PEX) After many secrets sold, and many plots ruined, you gain enough skills to be known as an expert spy.

You can advance to Master level after taking at least two Expert level spycraft. Each spycraft will cost you 200 PEX."
                PERKS {
                    #tp1GjIWPhRY145UVJ6Au5Zqq ^"Resistance - Torture" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All Spies can get this spycraft. An expert spy knows how to resist any kind of physical or mental torture. When resisting any kind of torture and interrogation, the Spy gets an advantage on Constitution and Wisdom saving throws, and Charisma (Deception) skill checks."
                    }
                    #tGiWkc7GwzflmmJYoGXcc6af ^"Resistance - Divination" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All spies can get this spycraft. An expert spy knows how to resist any divination magic or spelllike ability that is targeted to reveal its hiding place. When resisting any kind of divination magic that would reveal the spy’s physical position in the world, the spy gets advantage on its saving throw. If the effect does not require a saving throw, the agent gets one at the standard difficulty to resist such an effect."
                    }
                    #tLJamAjtnIVtPVYUAmZgHAdY ^"Resistance - Enchantment" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "All spies can get this spycraft. The spy is loyal to the cause it works for. You get advantage on your saving throws on any charm and enchantment magic that attempt to sway your mind away from your cause."
                    }
                    #tdIraXPGbTrsErKmzY0E0VXJ ^"Tools of the Trade - Magical" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 200
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "Each specialty gets different use of this spycraft:

Agent of the Government: The Agent of the Government gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp, and only the attuned Explorer can use it. This talisman is called Call of the Authority, and when you show this talisman to a loyal guardsman or official and activate its magic, this will compel the guardsman or official to act sympathetic towards you and aid you in a time of crisis. The talisman turns to dust after usage.

Free Agent: Free Agent gains a chance to purchase a special talisman for 100 gp and only the attuned Explorer can use it. This talisman is called Free Pass, and when you show this talisman to a corrupt guardsman or official and activate its magic, this will compel the guardsman or official to act sympathetic towards you, and aid you in a time of crisis. The talisman turns to dust after usage."
                    }
                }
            }
            #t3qXKG8OPUEsbjmHXCEeTzSh ^"Master Spy" DEF {
                EXTENDS ^"Profession Rank"
                ^"Rank Number"
                INTEGER 4
                ^"Description"
                STRING "(5000 PEX) You are at the top among most of your spy colleagues, always revered. There is nothing much you can learn about the trade, but you have much to share with your students."
                PERKS {
                    #tvI2yXg2b9SKyNf0S7pIhwHK ^"Stories of the Past:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "You have a lot of experiences, stories and have probably taken some part in many of the legends and myths. You have the ability to inspire greatness in others. You can grant inspiration to anyone who listens to your stories a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus daily. This inspiration point must be used in 1 hour or it will be lost. Anyone who already has an inspiration point won't be affected by this."
                    }
                    #t3KyewyZErX3XY8jts3qD99r ^"Leader of the Cell:" DEF {
                        EXTENDS ^"Profession Perk"
                        ^"PEX Cost"
                        INTEGER 0
                        ^"Description"
                        STRING "As the revered leader of a small cell that operates undercover, you can rely on your cell to provide you with certain benefits:

• Your cell standing will provide you with lavish lodging and food.

• The cell will pay for your resurrection if you ever need such a service. (You will owe to the cell)

• You will always have a cell-house provided to you in every city or town that houses similar operations.

• The cell has tremendous political power. If you are accused of a crime, the secret members of the cell will step up to support you.

• You can get access to powerful political figures through your cell. Such connections may require donations."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
